According to the NYT, based on incomplete reporting from states: 184,074 new cases today.
Because of high counts on Dec 20-22, the counts need to exceed an average of only 170,250 a day.
@belikewater

I had previously lowered my forecast on bin 2 a bit because I expect a severe dip in testing and reporting from Dec 25 to Jan ~4, relative to what cases would have been otherwise. But I also wonder whether some places might expand testing capacity over the holidays because of Omicron. If it weren't for the holidays, there'd be no question in my mind that 200k/day would be reached by the end of the year. So, for now, I'm raising my forecast on bin 2.
@Anneinak what do you think? Later edit: For Dec 21: New cases: 190,190; 7 day Average: 153,792 (+10,819): https://twitter.com/BNODesk/status/1473485023689035779
With an exponential fit, this would put us on track to reach a 7 day average of 200k on Dec 26. But, I think it's realistic to expect a big decline in new cases on Dec 25. So unless cases tick up even faster, bin 2 would require 200k to be reached after Christmas.
